High endothelial venules - High endothelial venules are specialized post-capillary venous swellings characterized by plump endothelial cells as opposed to the usual thinner endothelial cells found in regular venules.
High-energy visible light - In ophthalmology, high-energy visible light is high-frequency light in the violet/blue band from 380 to 500 nm in the visible spectrum.
Hepatitis E virus - Hepatitis E virus is the infective organism that causes hepatitis E.
